A '''bell tone''' is a musical technique in which a voice or instrument is made to imitate the sound of a [[bell (instrument)|bell]]. It is characterized by a strong opening [[articulation (music)|articulation]] followed by a rapid decay of sound.<ref>{{cite book|last=Maclagan|first=Susan J|title=A dictionary for the modern flutist|year=2009|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=9780810867284|page=15}}</ref>
