{{Infobox language |name=Cofán |nativename=''A'ingae'' |states=[[Ecuador]], [[Colombia]] |region=[[Oriente (Ecuador)|Oriente]] or Ecuadorian [[Amazon basin|Amazon]] |ethnicity= [[Cofán people]] |speakers=2,400 |date=2001–2008 |ref=e18 |familycolor=American |family=[[language isolate]] |nation=[[Ecuador]]: indigenous languages official in own territories |iso3=con |glotto=cofa1242 |glottorefname=Cofán }}
The '''Cofán language''' (also '''Kofan''' or '''Kofane'''; [[endonym|autonym]]: '''A'ingae''') is the language of the [[Cofán]] people, an [[Indigenous people|indigenous]] group native to the province [[Sucumbíos Province|Sucumbíos]] in northeast [[Ecuador]] and southern [[Colombia]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Fischer|first=R. W.|date=2007|title=Clause linkage in Cofán (A'ingae), a language of the Ecuadorian-Colombian border region|url=http://dare.uva.nl/search?identifier=f2bfbcc7-d480-4e9c-ac3a-78b4322ef021}}</ref>
While Cofán is an [[endangered language]], it is classified as a developing language with 1400 to 2400 speakers.<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?hl=en&lr=&id=fcFxAAAAQBAJ&oi=fnd&pg=PA221&dq=Cof%C3%A1n+language&ots=-KMfU6pxUz&sig=K1L7c04ewq-Sv29gpu_MjTyfRTU#v=onepage&q=Cof%C3%A1n%20language&f=false|title=Subordination in Native South American Languages|last=Gijn|first=Rik van|last2=Haude|first2=Katharina|last3=Muysken|first3=Pieter|date=2011-04-29|publisher=John Benjamins Publishing|isbn=9789027287090|language=en}}</ref> There are two types of Cofán: Aguarico (spoken in Ecuador) and San Miguel (primarily spoken in Colombia).<ref name=":0" /> Approximately 60% of Cofán speakers in Ecuador are [[Literacy|literate]] in their own language.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ethnologue.com/language/con|title=Cofán|work=Ethnologue|access-date=2017-08-23}}</ref>
Use of Cofán in Ecuador is connected to the language in land property rights documents and in the bilingual access to the language in schools. In Colombia, Cofán is more endangered because of war, displacement, and intermarriage.<ref name=":0" />
== Classification == Cofán is a [[language isolate]]. Some scholars claim Cofán is not classified into a [[language family]]. The language does exhibit some lexical similarities to [[Chibchan languages|Chibchan]], a geographically neighboring language. However, evidence of the lexical influence Chibchan has on Cofán does not prove any genetic relationship between the two languages.<ref name=":2">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?hl=en&lr=&id=GxMaDQAAQBAJ&oi=fnd&pg=PA157&dq=Cof%C3%A1n+language&ots=5GY1gHP-np&sig=Ojd3ZN5xL8zuwGBbhfodM4Ye24Y#v=snippet&q=Cofan%20&f=false|title=South American Indian Languages: Retrospect and Prospect|last=Klein|first=Harriet E. Manelis|last2=Stark|first2=Louisa R.|date=2011-07-20|publisher=University of Texas Press|isbn=9780292737327|language=en}}</ref>
== Phonology ==
=== Vowels === There are ten vowels in Cofán: five oral vowels and their nasal counterparts.<ref name=":3">{{Cite journal|last=Borman|first=M.B.|date=Summer 1962|title=Studies in Ecuadorian Indian Languages|url=|journal=Summer Institute of Linguistics of the University of Oklahoma|volume=7|pages=45–59|via=}}</ref>
{| class="wikitable" style="text-align: center;" ! &nbsp; !! [[Front vowel|Front]] !! [[Central vowel|Central]]!! [[Back vowel|Back]] |- ! [[Close vowel|Close]] | {{IPA|/i/, /ĩ/}} || {{IPA|/ɨ/, /ɨ̃/}} || |- ! [[Mid vowel|Mid]] | {{IPA|/e/, /ẽ/}} || || {{IPA|/o/, /õ/}} |- ! [[Open vowel|Open]] | || {{IPA|/a/, /ã/}} || |}
=== Consonants === As noted by Raphael Fischer and Kees Hengeveld, Cofán has a moderately large consonant inventory. A notable feature is the three-way voicing distinction for stops and affricates.<ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4">{{Cite journal|last=Fischer|first=Raphael|last2=Hengeveld|first2=Kees|date=|title=Cofán (A’ingae)|url=|journal=Amazonian Languages: An International Handbook|location=Berlin|publisher=de Gruyter Mouton|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref> {| class="wikitable" style="text-align: center;" ! colspan="2" | ![[Bilabial consonant|Bilabial]] ![[Labiodental consonant|Labiodental]] ![[Alveolar consonant|Alveolar]] ![[Postalveolar consonant|Post-alveolar]] ![[Palatal consonant|Palatal]] ![[Velar consonant|Velar]] ![[Glottal consonant|Glottal]] |- ! rowspan="3" |[[Stop consonant|Stop]] !{{small|[[Voiceless consonant|Voiceless]]}} |{{IPA|p}} | |{{IPA|t}} | | |{{IPA|k}} |{{IPA|ʔ}} |- !<small>[[Aspirated consonant|Aspirated]]</small> |{{IPA|pʰ}} | |{{IPA|tʰ}} | | |{{IPA|kʰ}} |- !{{small|[[Prenasalized consonant|Prenasalized]]}} |{{IPA|ᵐb}} | |{{IPA|ⁿd}} | | |{{IPA|ᵑɡ}} | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Fricative consonant|Fricative]] | |{{IPA|f}} |{{IPA|s}} |{{IPA|ʃ}} | |{{IPA|ɣ}}~{{IPA|ɰ}} |{{IPA|h}} |- ! rowspan="3" |[[Affricate consonant|Affricate]] !<small>[[Voiceless consonant|Voiceless]]</small> | | |{{IPA|ts}} |{{IPA|tʃ}} | | | |- !<small>[[Aspirated consonant|Aspirated]]</small> | | |{{IPA|tsʰ}} |{{IPA|tʃʰ}} | | | |- !<small>[[Prenasalized consonant|Prenasalized]]</small> | | |{{IPA|ⁿdz}} |{{IPA|ⁿdʒ}} | | | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Nasal consonant|Nasal]] |{{IPA|m}} | |{{IPA|n}} | |{{IPA|ɲ}} | | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Approximant consonant|Approximant]] | |{{IPA|ʋ}} | | |{{IPA|j}} | | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Flap consonant|Flap]] | | |{{IPA|ɾ}} | | | | |}
== Grammar == Word order in Cofán is mostly free and flexible and is influenced by pragmatic factors. (Co)subordinate clauses, however, have a strong preference for being predicate-final.<ref name=":4" />
Paragraphs are a distinct and important structure in Cofán grammar. There are fifteen different paragraph types used in Cofán narrative discourse. The narrative paragraph and simultaneous paragraph “form the backbone of narrative discourse.” The coordinate descriptive paragraph and deictic paragraph are used to portray character or participant identity development and to outline situations. Reason, contrast, and antithetical paragraphs are used to foster relationships and tension between speakers and events. Amplification paragraphs, contraction paragraphs, negated antonym paragraphs and cyclic paragraphs are used in “paraphrasing” particular information. Lastly, comment paragraphs and quote and dialogue paragraphs are used to add detail to a narrative.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Borman|first=M.B.|date=1977|title=Discourse Grammar: Studies in Indigenous Languages of Colombia, Panama, and Ecuador|url=|journal=Summer Institute of Linguistics|volume=52:3|pages=290–338|via=}}</ref>
== Orthography == A written system of the Cofán [[iarchive:rosettaproject con ortho-1|alphabet]] has been devised by M. B. Borman. Some are simple letters, while others are compound. Nasalization on vowels is orthographically represented by placing {{angbr|n}} after the vowel. (For example, /{{IPA|ã}}/ is written {{angbr|an}}.) Prenasalization on stops and affricates is orthographically represented either by placing {{angbr|m}} before bilabials (for example, {{angbr|mb}} for /{{IPA|ᵐb}}/) or by placing {{angbr|n}} elsewhere (for example, {{angbr|nd}} for /{{IPA|ⁿd}}/ and {{angbr|ng}} for /{{IPA|ⁿg}}/).<ref name=":1">{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/rosettaproject_con_ortho-1|title=Cofan cosmology and history as revealed in their legends|last=Borman|first=M. B.|date=1990-01-01|publisher=Instituto Linguistico de Verano}}</ref><ref name=":4" /> {| class="wikitable" style="text-align: center;" !Borman !IPA |- |a |{{IPA|a}} |- |b |{{IPA|b}} |- |c |{{IPA|k}} |- |cc |{{IPA|kʰ}} |- |ch |{{IPA|tʃ}} |- |chh |{{IPA|tʃʰ}} |- |d |{{IPA|d}} |- |dy |{{IPA|dʒ}} |- |e |{{IPA|e}} |- |f |{{IPA|f}} |- |g |{{IPA|g}}~{{IPA|ɣ}}~{{IPA|ɰ}} |- |i |{{IPA|i}} |- |j |{{IPA|h}} |- |m |{{IPA|m}} |- |n |{{IPA|m}} |- |ñ |{{IPA|ɲ}} |- |o |{{IPA|o}} |- |p |{{IPA|p}} |- |pp |{{IPA|pʰ}} |- |q |{{IPA|k}} |- |qq |{{IPA|kʰ}} |- |r |{{IPA|ɾ}} |- |s |{{IPA|s}} |- |sh |{{IPA|ʃ}} |- |t |{{IPA|t}} |- |tt |{{IPA|tʰ}} |- |ts |{{IPA|ts}} |- |tss |{{IPA|tsʰ}} |- |u |{{IPA|ɨ}} |- |v |{{IPA|ʋ}} |- |y |{{IPA|j}} |- |z |{{IPA|z}} |}
== Counting system == [https://mpi-lingweb.shh.mpg.de/numeral/Cofan.htm Cofán’s number system] is a base-five system. Cofán speakers use Spanish numerals to count.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mpi-lingweb.shh.mpg.de/numeral/Cofan.htm|title=Cofan|website=mpi-lingweb.shh.mpg.de|access-date=2017-05-01}}</ref>
