{{Infobox writer | name = Heydar Abbasi | image = | caption = | birth_date = 1943 | birth_place = [[Maragheh]], Iran | occupation = Poet, translator & writer | death_date = | death_place = | movement = | children = | }} '''Heydar Abbasi''' ({{lang-fa|حیدر عباسی}}), mainly known by his pen name, ('''Barişmaz''' ''':''' '''باریشماز'''), is an [[Iran]]ian poet, translator, writer and [[literary critic]] of [[Azerbaijani literature]].<ref name="Abbasi">{{cite encyclopedia |last=|first=| title= اعضای کمیسیون فرهنگی مجلس با شاعر مراغه ای دیدار کردند | encyclopedia=[[Irna]] | accessdate=June 2015|url=http://www.irna.ir/fa/News/81638689/}}</ref>
== Early life == Abbasi was born 1943 in [[Maragheh]], [[East Azerbaijan]]. He graduated from the [[University of Tabriz]] and later completed his postgraduate studies in Tehran.<ref name="Abbasi" />
== Works== The best known work is translate [[Nahj al-Balagha]] to [[Azerbaijani language]] by [[Arabic alphabet]] and Latin, also [[Masnavi]] to [[Azerbaijani language]] by Arabic alphabet and other works are as follows.<ref name="Abbasi" /> * Nəğmə Daği və Istimar * Kəbə və qanli azan * Güləndə hərzaman Məşair və şeytan * Səs * Duvarlar * Ödümlü Dirək * Çağirilmamiş qonaqlar * Müxannaslər * Val- əsr * Dartilmamiş dənlər
